images.name: Dan Campbell admits not knowing about Jared Goff's perfect game
images.caption: Lions coach Dan Campbell jokes about giving the game ball to another player after learning about Jared Goff's 18-for-18 performance against the Seahawks.

articles.description: Jared Goff didn't receive one of two game balls after his record-setting performance Monday night, but the Lions made amends Tuesday, giving the QB one after he went 18-of-18 passing in the win over Seattle.
articles.headline: Lions' Campbell makes amends, gives Goff game ball for record

images.name: FOR BARNWELL TRADES PIECE Las Vegas Raiders wide receiver Davante Adams enters the field before the game against the Carolina Panthers at Allegiant Stadium. [608x342]

images.name: Rodgers on Saleh 'hug moment': 'It's part of the learning process'
images.caption: Aaron Rodgers tells Pat McAfee that he has a great relationship with coach Robert Saleh despite viral "hug moment" on the sideline.

articles.description: Aaron Rodgers tried to quiet any talk that he and Robert Saleh don't get along, saying their relationship is "great." What's not so great is Rodgers' knee, which he said is "a little swollen" after loss to Broncos. He still expects to face the Vikings.
articles.headline: Jets' Aaron Rodgers: Relationship with Robert Saleh 'great'
